newsitem.title: AUSTRIA: Austrian bond futures tick higher, volume fades.
newsitem.headline: Austrian bond futures tick higher, volume fades.

text.p: 1630 GMT - Austrian bond futures tracked the German market higher on Wednesday but traders noted dwindling volume ahead of year-end holidays and forecast a period of range trading.
"It almost dried up completely at one stage," said a market participant, adding there was little willingness among investors to take on new positions.
* Latest 10 year benchmark 5.875 pct bond maturing July 2006 unchanged at 99.50 to yield 5.94 (5.94) pct in bourse trade, quoted post-market at 99.48/58 to yield 5.94/5.93.
* At the near end, five-year 5.50 percent bond maturing March 2001 up five bps at 103.00 to yield 4.74 (4.75) percent in bourse trade, quoted post-market at 102.99/103.07 to yield 4.74/72 percent.
* AGB future up 25 bps at 106.22 on turnover of 357 lots.
* 10-year spread to German bunds up one at seven bps, five-year spread down one at 18 bps.
* Money market rates mixed with three-month VIBOR steady at 3.350 and overnight money slightly higher at 3.00/3.25. -- Vienna newsroom, +431 53112 257
